  "text": "Stegopterna diplomutata differs from St. mutata in the following features ( Figs. 3, 4 , and 5): St. diplomutata is diploid and St. mutata is triploid. The floating inversions IL-1, IL-2, IL-3, IL-4, IIL-1 and IIL-2 have been found in St. mutata (see [CITATION_1] , whereas floating inversions IS-1, IL-5, IL-6 and IIL-2 have been found in St. diplomutata. It is conceivable that additional floating inversions may be found in other as-yet undiscovered populations of both species.",
